      "content_full": "This solution provides a robust function that ignores case and non-alphanumeric characters, which is the standard expectation for a palindrome checker.\n\n```python\nimport re\n\ndef is_palindrome(s: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Checks if a given string is a palindrome.\n\n    A palindrome is a sequence of characters that reads the same forwards and \n    backwards, ignoring case and non-alphanumeric characters.\n\n    Args:\n        s: The input string to check.\n\n    Returns:\n        True if the string is a palindrome, False otherwise.\n    \"\"\"\n    # 1. Normalize the string:\n    #    a. Convert to lowercase.\n    #    b. Filter out non-alphanumeric characters (keeping only letters and numbers).\n    # We use a generator expression and join for efficient filtering.\n    cleaned_s = \"\".join(char for char in s if char.isalnum()).lower()\n    \n    # 2. Check for palindrome property:\n    # Compare the cleaned string with its reverse (using slicing [::-1]).\n    return cleaned_s == cleaned_s[::-1]\n\n# --- Examples ---\n\n# Example 1: Simple palindrome\nprint(f\"'madam' is a palindrome: {is_palindrome('madam')}\")\n\n# Example 2: Case-insensitive palindrome\nprint(f\"'Racecar' is a palindrome: {is_palindrome('Racecar')}\")\n\n# Example 3: Palindrome with spaces and punctuation (Robust check)\nphrase1 = \"A man, a plan, a canal: Panama\"\nprint(f\"'{phrase1}' is a palindrome: {is_palindrome(phrase1)}\")\n\n# Example 4: Not a palindrome\nprint(f\"'hello world' is a palindrome: {is_palindrome('hello world')}\")\n\n# Example 5: Empty string (considered a palindrome)\nprint(f\"'' is a palindrome: {is_palindrome('')}\")\n```",
